# Netlify SPA fallback — serve the client-render shell for all non-prerendered routes.
# Use index.csr.html (a real <app-root> shell), NOT index.html: the latter is the
# prerendered "/" route, which is a meta-refresh redirect to /books, so using it as
# the fallback sends every cold deep-link (first-time visitors, shared links,
# incognito) to /books and loses the requested page. The CSR shell lets the Angular
# router read the deep URL and resolve it. Prerendered routes still win (Netlify
# serves the actual static file before this fallback).
